European stocks retreated, with the
Stoxx Europe 600 Index headed for its second weekly decline, as
the shares of basic resources companies and Merck KGaA fell.
U.S. futures advanced, while Asian stocks decreased.  The benchmark Stoxx 600 lost 0.3 percent to 260.38 at 8:08
a.m. in London, as all but two of 19 industry groups fell.
